ModelMapper
-> modelMapper is used to convert the objects(mapped) of class with each other
step1-add dependency of ModelMapper
<!-- https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/org.modelmapper/modelmapper -->
		<dependency>
			<groupId>org.modelmapper</groupId>
			<artifactId>modelmapper</artifactId>
			<version>3.1.0</version>
		</dependency>
step2- create method of modelmapper by using @bean
step3- create object of modelmapper with map(resource, class name )		

how to add validation 
step1 add dependency of validation (no need to add - <version>2.6.6</version>)
<!-- https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-starter-validation -->
<dependency>
    <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
    <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-validation</artifactId>  
</dependency>

step2- add the validation (bean annotation) on the field in entity class
step3- add @valid annotation in controller method where we apply validation  